## Available Tools

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| search_node | Search existing nodes by name or display name | Verify if a Rubyist or module already exists. When a match is found, use the exact name from the existing node ID to avoid creating duplicates |
| validate_module | Validate module name against curated lists | Uncertain about a module name's exact spelling or validity |
| search_edge | Search existing edges (relationships) | Check if a relationship between a Rubyist and a module already exists |
| search_observation | Search existing observations on edges | Verify if a relationship was already observed from the parent issue before extracting from a journal |
